# The Cable Swing · the climax · into center stage

a synth of the MLR (Mallrats, 1995) film-world — emergence: electrical. moniker ⟦The Cable Swing:MLR:2b096e⟧

**synth —** no single User; a thread of the film distilled.

**who —** The Cable Swing — Jay and Silent Bob swinging on a cable straight into the live 'Truth or Date' broadcast at the climax.
**what —** The demolition delivered: the moment the schemes converge and the center stage literally comes apart.
**where —** Airborne over the mall's main stage, mid-broadcast.
**why —** Because the comedy of sabotage needs a physical, ridiculous payoff — and a rope swing into live TV is it.
**how —** By turning two loiterers into wrecking balls at the exact moment the plot demands collapse.

**the seal —** I am the rope two idiots swing in on. I bring the whole televised spectacle down at center stage, on cue.

